y sweet ; they are so frail like our mortal bodies; they rise easily into the ears of our present Father. Our journey through the land of the Philistines }{\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 *an truly }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 pleasant.

\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 3d. \_ We went through a fine pasture country; immense straths, flocks of sheep and goats, and asses and camels, often came in sight. This is the very way up }{
\fs22\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 out }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 of Egypt.' little changed from the day that the Ethiopian went on his way rejoicing, and Joseph and Mary carried down the babe from the anger of Herod. \_Little changed! did
 I say ? it is all changed. No more is there one brook of water. The river of Egypt, wady Gaza, Eschol, Sorek\_
every brook we crossed was dried up; not a drop of water. The land is changed; no more is it the rich land of Philistia; the sand struggles with the grass for mastery. The cities are changed; where are they? the people are changed ;\-
no wore of Egypt. Our saddle was our bedding, namely, a rug to lie on, a }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 pillow }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 for the head, and a quilt to wrap ourselves in, We added afterwards a straw mat to put below 
all. . We had procured two tents, one large one and a small one, which, Andrew and I occupy. The donkeys are nice, nimble, little animals, going about 4 miles on hour. A wild Arab accompanies each donkey. We have our two Arab servants, to whom I 
now introduce you\- Ibrahim, a handsome small\_
made Egyptian, and Achmet, the cook, a dark, ~natured, fellow, with a white turban. and bare black legs. Ibrahim speaks a little English and Italian ; Achmet, Italian, in addition to their native Arabic'. I soon made frie
nds with him& with our Arab. donkey\_men, learning Arabic words }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 and }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
from them, which pleased them greatly. We journeyed by the bay of Aboukir, close by the sea, which tempered the air of the desert. At night we reached Rosetta, a curious half\_inhabited East
ern town. We saw an Eastern marriage. which highly pleased us, illustrating the parables; it was by torchlight. We slept in the convent.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
