Bazaar; saw the people praying in the mosque\_Friday being the Moslems' day of devotion. In the evening, we crossed the Nile in small boats, }{\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 which }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
mamma would abhor. It is a fine river; and its water, when }{\i\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 filtered, is }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 sweet and pleasant. We often thought upon it }{\i\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 in }{
\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 the desert. We slept that night on the sand }{\i\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 in our }{\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 tents by the sea\_shore.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
